article.description: Posley leads St. Bonaventure past Duquesne 92-75
article.headline: Posley leads St. Bonaventure past Duquesne 92-75
article.linkText: Posley leads St. Bonaventure past Duquesne 92-75
article.story: SAINT BONAVENTURE, N.Y. -- Marcus Posley hit six 3-pointers and scored 29 points on Saturday to lead St. Bonaventure to a 92-75 win over Duquesne. Andell Cumberbatch hit four 3s and had 18 points, Youssou Ndoye had 15 points and 11 rebounds and Dion Wright had 15 points and seven assists for the Bonnies (15-12, 8-8 Atlantic 10). Derrick Colter had 22 points and seven assists for the Dukes (10-17, 5-11) and Dominique McKoy had a career-high 20 points and 15 rebounds. Posley had 15 points in the first half and Ndoye and Cumberbatch split 22 as the Bonnies shot 51.6 percent, including 9 of 15 behind the arc, to lead 46-34 at the half. In the second half they made 24 of 35 free throws and finished 29 of 41 and 11 of 24 from long range. St. Bonaventure won the first meeting 100-97 in overtime with Posley scoring 36.
